wikipedia_page.main: Tommy Dunne (22 June 1946, in Glasgow – 2001) was a Scottish footballer who played as an inside forward. Dunne began his career in the mid-1960s with Leyton Orient, spending a short amount of time with the English side before returning to Scotland with Dumbarton. An equally short spell preceded a move to Albion Rovers, before a move to Dundee United towards the end of the decade. He then joined Scottish junior side Irvine Meadow in June 1971.
